{"build_type":"library","description":"AF_UNIX health-responder edge that confirms the rollback tool works as part of bring-up. Reads socket_path, rollback_bindir and rollback_binary from its request; first runs the test rollback by fork-exec of the rollback binary (verify-rollback-tool-still-loads) and only if it loads and runs cleanly (status zero) does it bind the pathname socket, listen, and serve (reusing the domain-agnostic accept loop + fixed-200 handler). If the rollback fails it exits without serving, so the kernel health client cannot get a 200 and the boot is not marked good. Thus a 200 from this edge means both the edge is up AND the rollback works. Pathname unix sockets cross the boundary AF_INET TCP could not.","module_name":"answer-health-request-through-pathname-socket","package_name":"answer-health-request-through-pathname-socket","function_definitions":{"answer-health-request-through-pathname-socket":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"__argc","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"__argv","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"five","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":5},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"addrsize","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":116},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","vari